https://codeforces.com/problemset/problem/855/B

Value of x is calculated as maximum of p·ai + q·aj + r·ak for given p, q, r and array a1, a2, ... an such that 1 ≤ i ≤ j ≤ k ≤ n. Help Snape find the value of x. Do note that the value of x may be negative.

Input
First line of input contains 4 integers n, p, q, r ( - 109 ≤ p, q, r ≤ 109, 1 ≤ n ≤ 105).

Next line of input contains n space separated integers a1, a2, ... an ( - 109 ≤ ai ≤ 109).

1)All PQR are positive 
    take max_element from array and multiply with PQR (max_element*P+max_element*Q+max_element*R)
2)else if negative element are present in PQR 
          negative(PQR)*min_element||negative(PQR)*min_element
          + Positive(PQR)*max_element||Positive(PQR)*max_element
          + Positive(PQR)*max_element||Positive(PQR)*max_element
          
